The paper deals with visual recognition tasks and proposes a method to improve the universality of representations learned on a source-task for transfer learning to multiple target-tasks. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the Computer Vision (cs.CV) sub-category. Additionally, the paper uses unsupervised learning and network architectures, which are common in the Machine Learning (cs.LG) and Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. The paper also mentions multiple domains and tasks, indicating that it may be relevant to the Natural Language Processing (cs.CL) sub-category. Finally, the paper uses network architectures, which are also relevant to the Neural and Evolutionary Computing (cs.NE) sub-category.
